TEXT 816 160 Left 2 ;S3: VCF Wave Select\nS3 = 0: Square\nS3 = 0.5: None\nS3 = 1: Ramp\n \nS4: Noise In\nS4 = 0: None\nS4 = 1: White Noise\n \nS6: VCF Modulation Source\nS6 = 0:   Low Frequency Oscillator\nS6 = 0.5: None\nS6 = 1:   Attack Delay Generator\n \nR28: Frequency\nR29: Resonance\nR38: Modulation Depth
TEXT 816 128 Left 2 !.include spdt.sub
TEXT 816 96 Left 2 !.param RMIN=1
TEXT -120 944 Left 2 ;CHANGE: R28 min needs ~5k in series, or investigate the zero causing high gain at low frequencies.\nCHANGE: R28 ought to be logarithmic, and should probably max out around 20 kHz (currently more like 10 kHz).\nCHANGE: WNS (S4 pathway) can probably be the same gain as the S3 pathway.\nCHANGE: R29 should be logarithmic and its specific role should be clarified.\nCHANGE: Control voltage useful input range and resulting cutoff frequency are very sensitive to Resonance.\nCHANGE: R38 has an overly complicated relationship with V_G of Q8\nCHANGE: Investigate a better tunable-resonance filter. Not sure why this one is designed with a quadratic zero.\nCHANGE: This block could have one input, switched external to the circuit. Gain control could be in here, too, instead of VCA.
